.TH RUN-ALFE-CONFORMANCE 1 "May 2026" "run-alfe-conformance" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
run-alfe-conformance \- run the alfe CLI conformance scenario corpus.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B run-alfe-conformance
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B run-alfe-conformance
walks the conformance scenario corpus under
.B autolisp-front-end/tests/scenarios/
and runs each scenario against a freshly-spawned
.BR alfe (1)
process, asserting that the exit code, stdout, and stderr match
the scenario's
.BR :expected-* " keys. "
Used by CI and as a manual regression-test driver after CLI changes.
.SH OPTIONS
See
.BR \-\-help
for the live option list. The corpus location, filter regex, and
summary verbosity are the typical knobs.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Every non-skipped scenario passed.
.TP
.B 1
One or more scenarios failed (the summary lists which).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR alfe (1).
.SH AUTHOR
Pascal J. Bourguignon and contributors.
